<task id="R3-084" project="spaarke-platform-foundations-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>`MembershipJunctionUpdater` handler (subscription consumer, idempotent)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completion-date>2026-06-22</completion-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Wave 21 Group S. Created IMembershipJunctionUpdater (Scoped handler contract — also reused
      directly by task 085's MembershipReconciliationJob) + MembershipJunctionUpdater (real impl,
      composite-alternate-key idempotency on the 5-tuple {personId, personIdType, entityLogicalName,
      entityRecordId, sourceField} — retrieve-then-create/update/delete branching, Added/Updated
      both upsert role+lastSyncedOn, Removed deletes-if-present and no-ops-if-absent) +
      MembershipJunctionUpdaterHost (Service Bus subscription consumer BackgroundService —
      DefaultAzureCredential per ADR-028, ServiceBusProcessor pump, AbandonMessageAsync on
      transient error, DeadLetterMessageAsync on JSON deserialization failure, 30s drain on
      StopAsync per NFR-07 with `DrainTimeout` constant locked at the type-system level) +
      NullMembershipJunctionUpdaterHost (ADR-032 hosted-service-peer pattern — logs once on
      start, performs no Service Bus work) + MembershipJunctionUpdaterOptions (bound from
      "Membership:JunctionUpdater" section, distinct from task 081's "Membership:EventPublisher"
      sub-key so the publisher + consumer kill-switches flip independently). Extended
      MembershipModule.AddMembership() with symmetric registration per bff-extensions.md §F.1:
      both Enabled=true and Enabled=false branches register an IHostedService (real or Null) —
      symmetric registration eliminates operator-flag-flip-time DI surprises. Updated
      appsettings.Development.json.template with "Membership:JunctionUpdater" subsection
      (Enabled=false by default; operator populates ServiceBusNamespace + flips Enabled to true
      after task 071 topic deploy completes). Tests: 14 new unit tests across
      MembershipJunctionUpdaterTests (12) + MembershipJunctionUpdaterHostTests (2) — all pass.
      Test coverage: Added_CreatesRowWhenMissing, Added_UpdatesWhenRowExists (idempotency on
      duplicate Added), Updated_OverwritesRoleAndLastSyncedOn, Updated_CreatesRowWhenMissing
      (recon self-heal), Removed_DeletesExistingRow, Removed_IsNoOpWhenRowAbsent (idempotency on
      duplicate Removed), DuplicateDelivery_IsIdempotent (canonical at-least-once duplicate-delivery
      test — stateful mock toggles row existence; verifies Create once + Update once on the second
      delivery), CancellationRequested_Propagates, NullEvent_Throws, NullHost_LogsAndReturnsImmediately,
      RealHost_StopAsync_DoesNotDeadlock_WhenNeverStarted, DrainTimeout_Is30Seconds (locks
      NFR-07 at the type level). Full BFF unit-test run: 7524 pass / 110 skip (pre-existing) /
      0 fail (1m30s). Build: 0 errors, no new warnings. Publish: 46.22 MB (+0.01 MB vs task 081
      baseline 46.21 MB — within +1 MB per-task ceiling; cumulative still well under 60 MB
      hard ceiling). CVE: pre-existing Microsoft.Kiota.Abstractions 1.21.2 HIGH only; no new HIGH
      CVEs introduced. Sub-agent boundary respected — no .claude/ writes. Coordinated with parallel
      sibling 081: no file overlap (081 owns Events/MembershipEventPublisher*, 084 owns the rest);
      both extend MembershipModule with distinct config sub-keys so the publisher (publish-side) +
      consumer (subscription-side) kill-switches are flipped independently. Topic + subscription
      names match task 071 Bicep: "sprk-membership-changes" + "recon-junction-updater".
      Cross-cutting: IMembershipJunctionUpdater is now available for task 085's
      MembershipReconciliationJob to reuse directly — recon synthesizes MembershipChangedEvent
      payloads from source-of-truth scans and invokes HandleAsync through the same idempotency
      contract, so a single write path (junction-row upsert/delete) services both event-driven +
      nightly-recon paths.
    </completion-notes>
